en_139586_0	Two persons have been arrested in connection with attacking an ambulance on its way to transport a patient during the joint opposition’s march.
en_139586_1	The Peradeniya police arrested the two persons who are residents of Hindagala and Medabowala in Peradeniya.
en_139586_2	Police said that the suspects who are aged 49 and 53 years respectively are scheduled to be produced at the Kandy Magistrate’s court today.
en_139586_3	While there was a  vehicle congestion on the Colombo – Kandy Road with the kick-off of the protest march from Peradeniya on 28th last month, a group had attacked the ambulance passing the place.
en_139586_4	However the police said that the action would be taken to arrest the remaining suspects using video footage.
